An in oral history of the 2009 VMAs, Billboard reveals P!nk gave Kanye West a piece of her mind following the infamous Taylor Swift interruption: <br />
<br />
&ldquo;P!nk walked up to him and got in his face...She was giving him her two cents about how fucked up this was and then stormed off.&rdquo;

Young Thug recently spoke out about people thinking he&rsquo;s gay during an interview, saying: <br />
<br />
&ldquo;If people think that I&rsquo;m gay, they already misjudged. I&rsquo;m the straightest man in the world&hellip;I hate guys. What the fuck are you talking about?&rdquo;

Billie Eilish says that Ariana Grande inspired her to continue making music.<br />
<br />
&quot;To be honest, the album &lsquo;Thank U, Next&rsquo; finally made me feel like writing again. And...for the first time in a long time, I felt the need to make music myself.&quot;

Taylor Swift says she's obviously &quot;pro-choice&quot; and pledges to defeat Trump by doing everything she can for 2020: <br />
<br />
&quot;We're a democracy &mdash; at least, we're supposed to be &mdash; where you're allowed to disagree, dissent, debate. I really think that [Trump] thinks this is an autocracy.&quot;

Lana Del Rey says when she&rsquo;s not writing, she just talks shit all day in Starbucks.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;I feel very much that writing is not my thing: I&rsquo;m writing&rsquo;s thing. When the writing has got me, I&rsquo;m on its schedule. But when it leaves me alone, I&rsquo;m just at Starbucks, talking shit all day&rdquo;

Taylor revealed that the hardest song to write was &quot;Soon You'll Get Better&quot; featuring the Dixie Chicks.<br />
<br />
&quot;That's a song I don't know if I'll ever play it live. It's just really difficult for me. It was hard to write. It's hard to sing. It's hard to listen to for me. But sometimes, music is like that. Sometimes it's not just about stuff that was pleasant to feel.&quot;

